[{"location":"#CitableParserBuilder-documentation","page":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","title":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","title":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","text":"The CitableParser package offers common functions and structures used by the Kanones.jl and Tabulae.jl packages for building ancient Greek and Latin morphological parsers, respectively.  (Kanones.jl and Tabulae.jl are not yet registered packages.)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Structures","page":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","title":"Structures","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","title":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","text":"LexemeUrn\nStemUrn\nRuleUrn\nFormUrn\nAnalysis","category":"page"},{"location":"#CitableParserBuilder.LexemeUrn","page":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","title":"CitableParserBuilder.LexemeUrn","text":"Abbreviated URN for a lexeme.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#CitableParserBuilder.StemUrn","page":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","title":"CitableParserBuilder.StemUrn","text":"Abbreviated URN for a morphological stem.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#CitableParserBuilder.RuleUrn","page":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","title":"CitableParserBuilder.RuleUrn","text":"Abbreviated URN for rule.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#CitableParserBuilder.FormUrn","page":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","title":"CitableParserBuilder.FormUrn","text":"Abbreviated URN for a morphological form.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#CitableParserBuilder.Analysis","page":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","title":"CitableParserBuilder.Analysis","text":"A citable morphological analysis.\n\nAn Analysis has five members: a token string value, and four abbreviated URNs, one each for the lexeme, form, rule and stem.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Functions","page":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","title":"Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","title":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","text":"abbreviate(urn::Cite2Urn)\nexpand(au::AbbreviatedUrn, registry::Dict)\nfstsafe(au::AbbreviatedUrn)","category":"page"},{"location":"#CitableParserBuilder.abbreviate-Tuple{Cite2Urn}","page":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","title":"CitableParserBuilder.abbreviate","text":"abbreviate(urn::Cite2Urn)\n\nConstructs an AbbreviatedUrn string from a Cite2Urn.\n\nExample:\n\njulia> abbreviate(Cite2Urn(\"urn:cite2:kanones:lsj.v1:n123\"))\n\"lsj.n123\"\n\nExample: a pipeline abbreviating a Cite2Urn and forming a LexemeUrn from the abbreviated string value.\n\njulia> Cite2Urn(\"urn:cite2:kanones:lsj.v1:n123\") |> abbreviate |> LexemeUrn\nLexemeUrn(\"lsj\", \"n123\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#CitableParserBuilder.expand-Tuple{AbbreviatedUrn,Dict}","page":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","title":"CitableParserBuilder.expand","text":"expand(au::AbbreviatedUrn, registry::Dict)\n\nConstructs a Cite2Urn from an AbbreviatedUrn and a dictionary mapping collection identifiers in  AbbreviatedUrns's to full Cite2Urns for a versioned collection.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#CitableParserBuilder.fstsafe-Tuple{AbbreviatedUrn}","page":"CitableParserBuilder documentation","title":"CitableParserBuilder.fstsafe","text":"fstsafe(au::AbbreviatedUrn)\n\nCompose SFST representation of an AbbreviatedUrn.\n\nExample:\n\njulia> LexemeUrn(\"lexicon.lex123\") |> fstsafe\n\"<u>lexicon\\.lex123</u>\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
